      "writtenOn": "2017-07-18T03:33:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Would it make more sense to do this in the InitializeThreads() loop instead of having it do its own loop?\n\nThis method could actually be a member on ProcessReader::Thread, and for that matter, so could InitializeThreadStack().\n\nFor that matter, with the current cascade-y structure (InitializeThreads -\u003e PtraceInitializeThreads -\u003e InitializeThreadStack), it’s a little non-obvious as to who’s calling what when. Maybe InitializeThreads() could be responsible for calling both Thread::InitializePtrace() and Thread::InitializeStack()?",
      "revId": "16bcf1e01044e139fc60dbd2152eb7f21cdcfa53",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
