      "message": "On other platforms, when we’ve suspended things, I think we subtract one to present the suspend count less our meddling. Since this all happens in OS-specific snapshot code, and “suspend count” is meaningless on Linux, I think we can drop the suspend_count field entirely here, and just return a hard-coded big fat zero from the Linux ThreadSnapshot::SuspendCount() when written.",
